\begin_layout Title
Simultaneous sensor and actuator placement for contaminant containment in
 water distribution networks
\end_layout

\begin_layout Abstract
Water distribution networks are acknowledged to be vulnerable
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "key-7"

\end_inset

, and there are multiple proposed ways of handling the hazard
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "key-4,key-5"

\end_inset

.
 A multi-objective mixed integer linear optimization formulation for simultaneou
sly finding sensor and actuator placement strategies for detection and containme
nt in water distribution networks is presented.
 This work assumes perfect, instant, digital sensors and actuators.
 The goal is to ensure observability of contaminants and prevent them from
 reaching demands.
 The formulation involves tracking the minimum time to detection for each
 vulnerable node and placing actuators beyond the compromised nodes at that
 time.
 Agreement with previous work's
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "key-6"

\end_inset

 results is seen.
 
\end_layout

